      "side": 1,
      "message": "linkat() is only available at all on OS X 10.10 and later. Chrome still needs to support 10.9. While this will be in the SDK, it won’t be present at runtime and will blow up.\n\nSince we probably don’t need to worry about older SDKs, you should be able to get away with just testing for linkat at runtime.\n\nHowever, this is awfully complex and I wonder why you don’t just use rename(). Is that just to prevent this from being used on directories? In that case, I’d ask why you didn’t elect to make this function (possibly renamed) work on directories too.",
      "revId": "3e9c385a1abaf70622414a19fc9a09170e1787c2",
